h: Two die in separate Road accidents in Goa
Two killed in Panaji, Chimbel Road accidents
21-yr-old dies in Road accident at Mapusa
Cops: 40% of deaths in Road accidents in 18-35 age group
sub_h: Over 40% of those who died in Road accidents last year were from the 18-35 age group, according to Goa police statistics. The data also reveals that most accidents take place between noon and 9pm.

h: 3 killed in two Road accidents in South Goa
sub_h: Three youngsters lost their lives in two separate accidents in Verna and Vasco on Sunday.

h: Nagoa man dead as Gujarati tourist's vehicle hits him
sub_h: A speeding Gujarati tourist on Friday rammed into the bike of a Nagoa man dropping his children to school, killing him and injuring the children.

h: 9% rise in 2022 Road accidents in Goa, 271 lives lost in 3,011 crashes
sub_h: In a shocking revelation, it has been found that two-third of the people who died in Road accidents in 2022 were on two-wheelers.

h: Study by Goa Medical College doctors finds 12.7% Road accidents due to alcohol consumption
sub_h: A study on road traffic accidents (RTAs) conducted by two doctors from the Goa Medical College and covering 440 cases found that a large number of drivers—13.04%—drove without a licence and that a sizeable number had consumed alcohol, thus placing themselves and others at risk.

h: Over 300 deaths/year: Booze kills more than Road accidents in Goa
sub_h: Even as alcoholism is a known problem in Goa, the sheer extent of the menace is disturbing, medical experts told TOI. Annually, Goa Medical College (GMC), the state's premier healthcare institute, sees over 300 deaths due to alcohol liver cirrhosis, a number comparable to road traffic accident deaths. In 2022, GMC reported 318 deaths due to alcoholic liver disease, and the previous year, it reported 356. Last year, Goa recorded 271 deaths.

h: Process for ex gratia payout for Road accidents made easy in Goa
sub_h: In a bid to provide financial relief to those families who applied but failed to get compensation due to delays or procedural lapses, the state government intends to offer ex gratia compensation of Rs 2 lakh to families of accident victims.

h: Process for ex gratia payout for Road accidents made easy
Maharashtra youth dies in Road accident at Usgao
Goa: Three die in Road accident at Canacona
sub_h: Several others sustained injuries – two among them are learnt to be critical – and are being treated in a hospital.

h: Goa: Sanguem locals protest after youth is killed in Road accident
sub_h: Irate residents of Sanguem resorted to a rasta roko on Thursday after Lavlesh Chari, 25, a resident of Cotarli, died after the motorcycle he was riding came under the wheels of a trolley truck at Cotarli, Sanguem, on Wednesday.

h: Two die in Road accident at Navelim
Goa: One killed, 8 injured in 3 Road accidents
sub_h: In three separate Road accidents in Ponda on Sunday, one person was killed and at least eight were grievously injured. At Par-Khandepar, Dhabal-resident Prakash Gaonkar, 55, was crushed to death by a tempo truck at 7.45pm. He was travelling towards Ponda on his scooter when he was knocked down by the speeding tempo and dragged for 50m, said officiating Ponda PI Sanjay Dalvi. The driver, Sachin Kharade, was arrested.

h: 65 Road accident black spots in Goa to be rectified in April
sub_h: In a bid to curb Road accidents in the state, the rectification of 65 black spots and accident-prone zones will be taken up in the first week of April, after a detailed audit that shall be conducted of each spot.

h: Mumbai man succumbs in Road accident in Margao
Disability activists want probe into rise in Road accidents
Couple killed in an Road accident at Raia
Goa: Traffic cell makes 500+ suggestions to government bodies to prevent Road accidents
sub_h: Pointing out that there have been over 100 fatal accidents in the state this year, Goa police’s traffic cell has dispatched letters to three government bodies with a combined 500-plus proposals to curb accident fatalities. “Till May 2022, a total of 1,348 s have been reported in Goa. The fatalities have increased by 27.9%, that is, 110 fatalities during the current year, as against 86 during the corresponding period in 2021,” traffic cell SP Shekhar Prabhudessai wrote to the director of panchayats, director of municipal administration and chief engineer of national highways.

h: One dies in accident near Kala Academy
Goa: 7 in North, 14 in South lose lives in Road accidents in February
sub_h: A total 1,740 challans were issued by the transport authorities for traffic violations in February.

h: Salcete records 15 Road accident deaths in January-September
sub_h: Fifteen people from Salcete lost their lives in the first nine months of this year in Road accidents, police records reveal.

h: 3 Kerala natives die in Sancoale Road accident
22-year-old dies in Road accident
Central Road accident database launched in Goa
sub_h: Taking a step towards road safety, the Goa government launched the Integrated Road accident Database (iRAD) project in the state on Wednesday.

h: One dies in Road accident at Mollem
Goa: Another cop killed in Road accident
sub_h: Head constable Sandesh Balsu Bhagat, 51, of Bhagatwada, Canacona, who had met with an accident while returning home from duty, succumbed to his injuries while undergoing treatment at Goa Medical College (GMC).

h: Goa: Five fatalities in four Road accidents in 24 hours
sub_h: A total of four fatal Road accidents over a period of 24 hours have claimed five lives and left one injured. While two of these accidents involved two-wheelers, the rest involved four-wheelers. All four cases were that of self-accidents according to the traffic cell.

h: Goa: Woman dies in accident at Verna
sub_h: A 39-year-old woman from Curchorem died on the spot in a Road accident at Verna, after the car she was driving crashed into a parked trailer truck on NH 17A. Verna police said that two other occupants, who were also in the car, are undergoing treatment.

h: Man killed in Road accident at Aldona
sub_h: Karnataka native Basappa Holikar, 28, died in an accident at Aldona on Saturday. He lost control of the motorbike he was riding and banged into a wall of the Corjuem bridge.

h: Bogda man dies in Road accident
Two killed in Road accident in Goa's Usgao
sub_h: Two persons were killed on Wednesday morning in a hit-and-run accident at Usgao. The accused is yet to be traced.

h: 59-year-old woman dies in Road accident
21-year-old loses life in Road accident at Borim

Margao man dies in Road accident
sub_h: Santosh Nipanikar, 55, a resident of Pajifond, Margao, died after the two-wheeler he was riding skidded off the road and landed in a gutter at Raia on Monday.

h: North Goa MP Shripad Naik injured, wife and PA killed in Road accident in Karnataka
sub_h: Union minister and North Goa MP Shripad Naik’s wife Vijaya and his personal assistant were killed while he was injured in a Road accident late Monday when they were returning to Karnataka’s Gokarna after visiting the Gante Ganapati temple at Yellapur.

h: Goa: Road accidents up in Dec & Jan, but fewer deaths
Man dies in accident on way to doctor
sub_h: A resident of Catebaga, Poinguinim, identified as Marshal D’Souza, 48, was declared brought dead when he was referred to the Canacona community health centre (CHC) after he met with an accident on Tuesday.

h: Goa: First 8 months of 2020 see marked drop in Road accident fatalities
sub_h: A slew of Covid-induced restrictions resulted in fewer people venturing out of their homes, consequently bringing down Road accident deaths in Goa roughly by one quarter during the first eight months of 2020. Earlier, the state would witness one such casualty every day on an average.

h: Maha woman dies in Road accident on Mandovi bridge
Two-wheeler riders hurt in Bicholim accident
2018 stats point to drop in Road accidents, rise in prosecutions
Goa: Power department staff killed in road mishap
sub_h: Santosh Kadekar, 48, was killed in a Road accident at Savoiverem Volvoi on Sunday afternoon. He was a line-helper, attached to the Ponda subdivision of the electricity department.
